                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> No, Kania<br /><br />The people I am talking about ARE necromancers.  Davood is a necromancer on the Rathe.  I like Davood.  He's a great guy and has been a great help to me.  I'm not saying that he's done anything at all wrong.  I'm simply using him as an example of why charm is overpowered.<br /><br />I am qualified to voice my opinion.  I've seen first-hand how effective charm is in CoD, in PoS, in BoT, and in HoH.  In several cases I have tagged along, both as a necro and as a cleric.  I've seen the techniques.  I've seen the risk involved.  Given a couple of levels and a spell (Being a twink necro I don't bother, since our guild's mains don't all have the 65 charm yet) I could do it.  Risk?  Sure.  The reward outstrips it though. If it didn't, then why would it be such a big deal that everyone's threatening to quit the game over it?<br /><br />And yes, he does use it in CoD.  So does a necromancer from my own guild, Mordicai.  So do others.  I was simply providing examples of cases that I know of.<br /><br />It's not a 'whine'.  It's a statement of fact.  This happens.  My opinion is that it is grossly overpowered.  Sony/Verant has never to my knowledge minced so long over such a necessary adjustment to the game.  Hell, my main class (Cleric) was given a lousy hammer at level 56 that let the best geared of us manage (Gasp) 45 DPS or so.  We could actually solo certain level 35-46 blue mobs within a 3-4 minute timeframe and a moderate amount of downtime... if we had the best gear in the game.  It took Verant less than 8 hours to nerf that into nonexistance, yet for months now the charm classes have steadily grown to dominate the PoP XP game to the point that anything else is laughable by comparison.<br /><br />And pre-65 don't tell me that your charm was that great.  I did plenty of charm killing in the Grey.  I never massed an AA point every 45 minutes. :P</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
